article.description: N. Florida routs NAIA Webber International 109-64
article.headline: N. Florida routs NAIA Webber International 109-64
article.linkText: N. Florida routs NAIA Webber International 109-64
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Aaron Bodager scored 18 points and four others reached double figure-scoring as North Florida defeated NAIA Webber International 109-64 Thursday night. The 109 points are a Division-I record for North Florida. The Ospreys (3-3) dropped 15 3-pointers with Bodager hitting five of eight, Beau Beech and Sean Brennan hitting four each. Bodager scored 12 of his points in a break-away first half. Romelo Banks and Brennan each scored 14 and Dallas Moore and Beech each scored 12 for the Ospreys. Sean Jowers (18 points) and Carlos Holey (10) sparked the Warriors (1-5) early, scoring eight each in the first half. The Ospreys opened the game in a Chris Davenport dunk and sped out 8-1. Webber International scrapped back as Jowers and Holey combined for three 3-pointers to tie at 18-18. But then came a nearly 13-minutes stretch of missed shots and turnovers while North Florida surged ahead 51-30 at halftime.
